title.rendered: Namibia vs Netherlands, Qualifier, T20 World Cup: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Pitch Report

Matches played in this edition 2

1st innings average score: 137

2nd innings average score: 110

Type: Even contest between the bat and ball.

Time: October 18, 9.30 AM IST

Teams

Probable XI for Namibia: Michael van Lingen, Divan la Cock, Stephan Baard, Jan Nicol Loftie-Eaton, Gerhard Erasmus (c), Jan Frylinck, JJ Smit, David Wiese, Zane Green (wk), Bernard Scholtz, Ben Shikongo

Probable XI for Netherlands: Max ODowd, Vikramjit Singh, Bas de Leede, Tom Cooper, Colin Ackermann, Scott Edwards (c & wk), Roelof van der Merwe, Tim Pringle, Logan van Beek, Fred Klaassen, Paul van Meekeren

Also Read:

Scotland vs Ireland, Qualifiers, T20 World Cup 2022: Fantasy Cricket Tips

Form Concerns

In the only four T20Is Vikramjit Singh has played in his career, he has scores of 15, 1, 3, and 10.

In 2022, Tom Cooper has been dismissed for a single-digit score on 5 out of 8 occasions.

Game Changers

Although Bas de Leede could add only 14 with the bat against Sri Lanka, his 3-wicket haul helped him ease into the Ultimate Team on My11Circle.

Scott Edwards has the ammunition to provide bonus points for his clean striking. He has registered scores of 26*, 7, 20, 26*, and 16* in his last 5 T20Is.

Smart Picks

Ben Shikongo turned out to be a dark horse in fantasy leagues in the game against Sri Lanka. Besides adding 20 points for 2 wickets, he generated 4 vital points for bowling a maiden over.

If not with the bat, Roelof van der Merwe does the job with the ball. He is also the best fielder in the Netherlands team.

Stephan Baard’s role is to accelerate the scoring in the powerplay. He has collected 120 runs, including a half-century in his last 5 T20Is.

Power Players                  

44 runs with the bat, followed by a two-for, earned Jan Frylinck the Player of the Match award against Sri Lanka.  His 50 points were the most in the match.

Lately, Fred Klassen has been consistently providing Netherlands with regular wickets. He has bagged 10 wickets, including the best figures of 5 for 19 in his last 5 T20Is.

David Wiese might not convert his promising starts into big scores, he remains the No.1 strike bowler for Namibia. He has taken 7 wickets in his last 3 competitive T20 games.

Fantasy Tip of The Day

For Namibia, there are quite a few utility cricketers who are capable of producing the goods with both bat and ball. Drafting them in your fantasy teams is likely to keep you in the hunt.
